SIMPLE: site
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Site
<hw>Site</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>situs</ets>, fr.
<ets>sinere</ets>, <ets>situm</ets>, to let, p. p. <ets>situs</ets>
placed, lying, situate: cf. F. <ets>site</ets>. Cf.
<er>Position</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The place where anything is
fixed; situation; local position; <as>as, the <ex>site</ex> of a city or
of a house</as>.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place fitted or chosen for any certain permanent
use or occupation; <as>as, a <ex>site</ex> for a church</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The posture or position of a thing.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The semblance of a lover fixed⟦br⟧
In melancholy <qex>site</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sited</ent>⟦br⟧
